Create Groups of Endpoints

Source: R/new_group.R
groups.Rd

Convenience function to quickly access various CMS data endpoints. Mostly for debugging purposes.

Usage

new_group(
  member_names,
  group_name = NULL,
  quick_call = FALSE,
  offset = 0,
  limit = 10
)

quick(x, offset = 0, limit = 10000, call = caller_env())

Arguments

member_names

<chr> Alias representing the CMS data endpoint.

group_name

<chr> Name of the group.

quick_call

<lgl> call quick_() method on group if TRUE.

offset

<int> The offset for pagination. Default is 0.

limit

<int> The maximum number of records to retrieve. Default is 10000.

x

<chr> Alias representing the CMS data endpoint or category.

call

Call environment. Default is the current environment.

Value

S7 class_group object.

A data frame or list containing the requested CMS data.
